Blurb::
Run Matlab through a direct interface - requires special Dakota build
Description::
Dakota supports a :ref:`library-linked interface to Matlab <advint:existingdirect>`, but it must be
explicitly enabled when compiling Dakota from source.  Contact the
Dakota users mailing list for assistance building and using Dakota
with these interfaces.

The :dakkw:`interface-analysis_drivers` specifies a Matlab file which
implements the parameter to response mapping.
Topics::

Examples::
See ``dakota/share/dakota/examples/users/MATLAB/linked``
